meanings.definition: A habitational surname from a place name, such as Saint-Roch in France.
Saint Roch (c. 1295 – 1327), a Christian saint, a confessor especially invoked against the plague.
meanings.english_definition: Saint Roch (c. 1295 – 1327), a Christian saint, a confessor especially invoked against the plague.

etymology.value: From the French place name Saint-Roch.
